<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>Part one is compulsory for every student taking the test. Students have to write a letter (120-150 words) or an email related to an input of up to 160 words.</p>
<p>How to do it</p>
<p>First read carefully the instructions and the notes provided</p>
<ul>
<li>Opening salutation: Both emails and letters should include it in accordance with the degree of formality required.</li>
<li>Paragraphing: Make sure your paragraphs are well structured taking into account the different ideas you are dealing with.</li>
<li>Closing phrasing: Both emails and letters should include it in accordance with the degree of formality required.</li>
</ul>
<p>In order to write your e-mail you may need some of these phrases:</p>
<p>Ways of starting and finishing e-mails:</p>
<table style="border-width: 0px; border-collapse: collapse;" border="1" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="-1">
<tbody>
<tr valign="top">
