<p>Ways of starting the first paragraph:</p>
<ul>
<li>Thank you for your e-mail</li>
<li>I’m writing to...</li>
</ul>
<p>Sentences at the end:</p>
<ul>
<li>I’m looking forward to seeing/ hearing... (informal)</li>
<li>I look forward to... (formal)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Activity 1: Read the following task and write your answer in 120-150 words in an appropriate style. Then, send it to your teacher for assessment.</b></p>
<p>You are organising meetings in the school where you work and recently you are inviting people to speak to students about healthy habits. You have received an e-mail form a doctor, James Smith, who you invited to speak on the 5th of May. Read his e-mail and the notes you have made. Then write an e-mail using you notes:</p>
<p>“I would love to speak to your students at the school. I cannot manage the 5th of May. Can you suggest any other day? (1)</p>
<p>Also, what aspects of health do you think students will find more interesting? (2)</p>
<p>I can show a short film about health and young people, let me know if there’s a projector available. (3)</p>
<p>Finally, could you tell me a bit about the type of audience I can expect? (4)</p>
<p>Thank you,</p>
<p>James Smith”</p>
<p>Your notes:</p>
<p>(1) Either the 7th or 9th</p>
<p>(2) Give him ideas</p>
<p>(3) There is a projector</p>
<p>(4) Number of students and age</p>
</div>
